latestPosts.caption:
From Banaras to the World Stage.
And from the past… came my power.

I’m beyond honoured to share that I’ve been selected as a finalist for Mrs. World International. But what I wear to the finale tells a story far bigger than me.

This outfit isn’t just fabric — it’s a legacy.
Made by reimagining two heirloom sarees — one from the North, one from the South — woven with memories, re-stitched with meaning, and reborn with purpose.

In a world that moves fast and forgets faster, I chose to stand still…
To honour my roots.
To celebrate sustainability.
To show that beauty doesn’t have to cost the planet.

This isn’t just fashion.
It’s a quiet revolution in six yards.

Join me on this journey — as a woman, a mother, a daughter of Banaras — carrying culture, craft, and consciousness to a global stage.

Thank you @rakshitha_manivannan for creating something that I can take forward to the next generation . You are amazing .Couldn’t have asked for something more .

Thank you @rahultoppo_7 for bringing this to life . We gave you literally no time , but you have weaved your magic to create this spectacular dress.

Thank you @tanvinimbalkar for believing in me and enrolling me in this . I woudnt even have thought of this otherwise . #newgoals 

Makeup and Hairstyle by @tressart_salon . You folks are awesome . Thanks for making me look the hundred percent .
